{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"07978b00-ec37-4e2b-93ec-f92601fea29a","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_wkN6pXCoj2kvnvS5L5VbzV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-eb91a9b1c5fb44d8b4d5d169a0c55f8a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-eb91a9b1c5fb44d8b4d5d169a0c55f8a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f3ed6597-ed4d-4daf-b326-2db021698903","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference things defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the .fsproj file:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), and `Program.fs` depends on both. So the correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` first (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` second (depends on Domain)\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` third (depends on Domain and Services)\n\nI need to fix the file order in the .fsproj.","outputTokens":473,"requestId":"DBD9:29F112:154C6B9:17DEDF3:69FD3383"},"id":"2604ec62-b3b7-4841-ad20-6533128b480d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:23.522Z","parentId":"58335e6f-2d22-40ed-8e5d-5febc71a9e23"}
